### Description
The **Aggregate Shipments (SA) **task allows to define distribution rules to relocate shipments and documents in the flows based on business rules through aggregation.

> Note

It is also possible to enable the aggregation of shipments and define an aggregation query in the [**Distribute Hybrids (SA)**](/doxee-platform/docs/distribute-hybrids-sa-batch-workflow-task-reference)** **task configuration.

### Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Input &gt; Reference file **section, click **Configure **to display the configuration fields.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the **File **field, upload a sample Staging &amp; Aggregation input resource, so that the system understands the XML format that is being used.

- In the **Shipment element **field, specify the element that identifies the shipment (for example: */FILE/SHIPMENT*).

- In the **Document element **field, specify the element that identifies the document (for example: */FILE/SHIPMENT/DOCUMENT*).

- Click **Save **to confirm.

> Tip

Once this section is configured, it is possible to download the loaded sample XML file, and view the list of the configured elements and attributes; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,) 

- In the **Query **field, you may enter the following queries:

**GROUP BY **[*criteria*]

- **ORDER BY **[*criteria*] **ASC **| **DESC**

> Important

The query must contain at least one statement.

> Note

The system will use the configured attributes to provide contextual suggestions when building queries. The query syntax is:

`GROUP BY argument [, argument] *
ORDER BY argument ASC|DESC [, argument ASC|DESC] *`For example:

`GROUP BY foo
ORDER BY bar ASC`The task will rearrange the shipments (and the contained documents) according to the specified query.
